links.displaytext: Paying the Bill - Other Types of Payment
Financial Aid is a Payment Method
Financial Aid as Payment - Title IV Permissions

In this scenario, a student is emailing Buckeye Link to inform us that they received an external scholarship. When this occurs, we should provide instructions on how to submit the scholarship to OSU and that their award summary may be adjusted.

Hi,

I received a $1,000 scholarship from my church. What is the address to send the check to? My donor asked me to contact you to ask.

Thanks.

Hi Jake,

Thank you for contacting Buckeye Link. Congratulations on the receipt of the scholarship award! 

External scholarship checks should be made out to The Ohio State University and include the student’s name and OSU ID number. Checks should be sent to:
Office of the University Bursar 
The Ohio State University 
P.O. Box 183248 
Columbus OH 43218-3248 
Once Ohio State receives the funds, the student’s financial aid package may be revised to include the amount of the scholarship. As a student cannot be awarded beyond the cost of attendance, we must include the scholarship amount in their financial aid package.

Please let me know if you have any additional questions.
When you are working with a student, it’s important that you review their account holistically.
Hello, I made a payment with my credit card. Can you tell me if the payment went through?

Yes, I see that your Discover card payment has posted successfully and your balance is now $0. I also noticed that you are enrolled in 6 credit hours. Since you’re enrolled at least half-time, which is 4 or more credit hours, you may be eligible for federal loan funding. Is this something you need information on?
I didn’t realize that a federal loan could be an option. I have been paying my balance with my credit card. I’d love to hear more about the loans. Thanks!
By taking a holistic approach to counseling, we can help students make informed decisions about their academics and their finances.
